HEADWORD: Whitewall
<hw>White"wall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The spotted flycatcher; -- so called from the white color of the
under parts.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

